crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a Remote Access Trojan (RAT). It establishes command-and-control (C2) communication with the hardcoded domain `jdkgradle.com` over a path `/jdk/update/update.php`. The malware can execute arbitrary shell commands via `popen` (e.g., using `"%s >/dev/null 2>&1 &"`), upload and download files, and receives commands to terminate itself. C2 traffic is encrypted using a hardcoded XOR key (`wLqfM]%wTx`~tUTbw>R^`) and Base64.
